    <h3>7.5.2.7 Example  (J2000/1/8)</h3>
    Which quantity is not necessarily the same for satellites that are in
    geostationary orbits around the Earth?<br />
    <br />
    A    angular velocity                    C    kinetic energy<br />
    B    centripetal acceleration         D    orbital period<br />
    <br />
    Answer C: Kinetic energy is dependent on the satellite's mass and velocity.
    Hence different satellites of different masses may have different kinetic
    energies.<br />
    <h3>7.5.2.8 Example</h3>
